# Feature 1: Session High Score Storage

## Summary

Store the highest score achieved during the current browser session. Persists only while the tab is open. Only games starting from Level 1 are eligible for high scores.

---

## Objectives

1. Store high score in sessionStorage
2. Display on start screen and game over screen
3. Track score, initials, level reached, timestamp
4. Enforce Level 1 start requirement for eligibility
5. Provide clean API for Feature 2 (Initials Entry)

---

## Data Model

```typescript
interface HighScoreData {
  score: number;
  initials: string;         // "---" if not set
  level: number;            // Level reached (0-indexed)
  timestamp: number;        // When achieved
  startedAtLevel: number;   // Must be 0 for eligibility
}
```

